/workspace/docs/USAGE.md-6-results to a git branch.\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md-7-\n--\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md-743-cloche workflow <name> [--project <dir>]\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md-744-```\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md-745-\ndocs/USAGE.md:746:List all workflows or render a specific workflow as an ASCII-art graph.\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md-747-\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md-748-| Flag | Default | Description |\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md-749-|------|---------|-------------|\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md-750-| `--project <dir>`, `-p` | current directory | Project directory to search for workflows. |\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md-751-\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md-752-With no arguments, lists all workflows grouped by type (container or host). With a\ndocs/USAGE.md:753:workflow name, renders the workflow graph showing step boxes, wiring, and result paths.\ndocs/USAGE.md-754-Wires are colorized: green for `success`, red for `fail`/`failed`,\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md-755-blue/yellow/orange/magenta for other results. Wires to the same destination are merged\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md-756-for readability.\n--\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-1-# Workflows\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-2-\ndocs/workflows.md:3:Cloche workflows define a directed graph of steps connected by named results.\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-4-\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-5-## Workflow Locations\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-6-\n--\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-56-\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-57-| Concept  | Description                                                        |\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-58-|----------|--------------------------------------------------------------------|\ndocs/workflows.md:59:| workflow | A named graph of steps connected by result wiring                  |\ndocs/workflows.md-60-| step     | A unit of work (inferred: `prompt` = agent, `run` = script)        |\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-61-| result   | A named outcome reported by a step (e.g. \"success\", \"fail\")       |\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-62-| wiring   | Maps a step's result to the next step, with optional output mappings |","numLines":142}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_019YC36ACaDRrMvZbHXWYBoe","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The key documentation file to update is `docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md`, specifically the \"DAG rendering\" section (lines 159-176). The current documentation describes:\n\n1. A merge bus with dashed horizontal lines for terminal wires\n2. Non-success wires using `dag-edge-nonsuccess` class with reduced opacity and a single failure color\n\nBut the actual implementation now uses:\n1. Wire columns (vertical paths) for non-success terminal wires, not a merge bus with dashed lines\n2. A color system with per-result colors: green for success, red for failure, blue/yellow/magenta/cyan/orange for other results\n\n\n3. Link node dots positioned at wire column intersections, with colored arrowhead markers that match each wire's color","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4416,"cache_read_input_tokens":36362,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4416},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1207efea-6ac7-4521-ac6e-5b4bb72a9855","uuid":"a3c1f332-5511-4aff-bf14-7960aafc80ff"}
